Some os the mostproblematic champs in the game history:

{{champion:268}}  {{champion:429}} {{champion:13}} {{champion:81}} {{champion:223}} {{champion:3}} {{champion:163}} 


The ones you listed are far away from being as problematic as the ones I listed.

the only instance I can recall is twisted fate.  He was basically the first and last attempt at it until {{item:3302}}  (which basically just gives the support a fighting chance though it can be abused unfortunately) and then later {{champion:555}} 

it's a big difference though as pyke can increase anyone nearby's gold compared to the relatively obscure procs of the relic shield line.  Pyke essentially doubles the kill-value of his target if he's successful and an ally is nearby

I actually had a lot of fun in those rare instances I shared a dual-relic shield lane XD  I'm not sure how much of a gold advantage it might have been though
